# .gitignore.SSF — Servant of the Sacred Fire
# Ptolemy Project — IP Protection Layer
# Created: 2026-04-18
# Author: Cody Michael Allison (michaelrendier)
#
# This file protects implementation IP during the First Age.
# Contents of this layer are never committed to public-facing branches.
# Released when Second Age conditions are met:
#   — T conjecture formally resolved
#   — d* gap closed
#   — arXiv preprint timestamped
#   — Nature/PRL submission submitted
#
# Three-layer gitignore architecture:
#   .gitignore          — community/public rules (committed)
#   .gitignore.SSF      — Sacred Fire IP layer (this file — committed, protects contents)
#   .git/info/exclude   — machine-local rules (never committed)
#
# Named artifact. Named timestamp. Named author. This is not an accident.
# The claim is already timestamped in the commit history.
# The Sacred Fire is carried, not hidden.

# ── SMNNIP reference implementation ──────────────────────────────────────────
# The SMNNIP derivation engine is the proof. The interface (phila.py) is public.
# The implementation is not.
Philadelphos/ptolemy_core_impl.py
Philadelphos/smnnip/
Philadelphos/julius_caesar/weights/
Philadelphos/julius_caesar/*.pt
Philadelphos/julius_caesar/*.bin
Philadelphos/julius_caesar/*.safetensors

# ── HyperWebster addressing implementation ────────────────────────────────────
# Horner's method bijection + octonion addressing + HYPER_KEY operations
# The data format (LLM_Datatype_Cl.py) is public. The addressing engine is not.
Callimachus/HyperWebster-Data-Storage/hwas_engine.py
Callimachus/HyperWebster-Data-Storage/octonion_address.py
Callimachus/HyperWebster-Data-Storage/horner_bijection.py

# ── KCF-1 implementation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kryptos Complexity Factor formal implementation
# The spec (docs/Kryptos/) is public. The cipher implementation is not.
Kryptos/Ciphers/KCF1/
Kryptos/kcf_impl.py
Kryptos/kcf_profiles/

# ── HYPER_KEY operations ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any file performing charset permutation as cryptographic key
*hyper_key*
*HYPER_KEY*

